            <ObservedData>
              <Attribute Type="Description">In a 22-year-old woman (patient 5) with erythrokeratoderma (EKVP7; 619209), born of unaffected consanguineous Hispanic parents, Duchatelet et al. (2019) identified homozygosity for a 1-bp deletion (c.112delT, NM_022121) in exon 1 of the PERP gene, causing a frameshift predicted to result in a premature termination codon (Ser38LeufsTer52). Quantitative RT-PCR of RNA from patient keratinocytes revealed marked reduction of PERP expression compared to control, consistent with nonsense-mediated decay. Immunostaining for desmosomal components showed expanded expression of FLG (135940) and KRT14 (148066), as well as increased nuclear localization of LOR (152445), suggesting a potential defect in terminal differentiation.</Attribute>
